When generating or refactoring Python code, follow the Google Python Style Guide (https://google.github.io/styleguide/pyguide.html).  Adhere to its conventions for:
    * Indentation: 4 spaces per level
    * Maximum line length: 80 characters
    * Naming: snake_case for functions and variables; PascalCase for classes
    * Import order: standard library, third-party, then local imports
    * Docstrings: Google style with Args, Returns, Raises sections
    * Whitespace: blank lines around top-level definitions and between methods